{# Anthology Atlas (#1124, #1129). Promoted out of soft launch (#1134): now
   indexed (no noindex), in the sitemap (no eleventyExcludeFromCollections),
   in site search (no data-pagefind-ignore), and signposted from the Anthology
   in every locale. Still EN-only. The graph is the real
   /data/anthology-atlas.json, projected from paperIndex.js at build time.
   Sibling of the NetSec Atlas (people); this one maps papers. #}
{# First-visit pre-paint reveal: stamp html.atlas-welcome before the welcome
   strip is parsed, so it occupies its space from the first frame instead of
   popping in when the deferred atlas script runs (the anti-CLS trick from the
   NetSec directory). anthology-atlas.js reconciles the hidden attribute and
   drops the class once it takes over, and on dismissal. #}
<script>
  (function () {
    try {
      if (localStorage.getItem('eiss-atlas-tour-seen') !== 'true') {
        document.documentElement.classList.add('atlas-welcome');
      }
    } catch (e) {}
  })();
</script>
<div class="atlas-shell">
  <a class="atlas-back" href="/anthology.html">&larr; The Anthology</a>
  <div class="atlas-masthead">
    <h1>Anthology Atlas</h1>
    <span class="atlas-proto-pill">Prototype</span>
    <button class="atlas-help" type="button" id="atlas-help" title="Take a tour" aria-label="Take a tour">?</button>
  </div>
  <p class="atlas-lede">A map of the <strong>European Security Studies Anthology</strong> — every paper presented at an EISS conference or workshop since 2017, drawn toward the <strong>research themes</strong> it touches. Each labelled <strong>hub is a theme</strong>; each <strong>dot is a paper or an author</strong>. Read it two ways: the <strong>Papers</strong> lens draws one dot per paper, coloured by <strong>edition year</strong>, so multi-theme papers settle between hubs and the field's thematic bridges become visible; the <strong>Authors</strong> lens draws one dot per author, sized by their paper count, with <strong>co-author edges</strong> on top so collaboration clusters settle out. Solid dots are papers with an Anthology page; hollow rings are programme entries without one yet. Filter by year or spotlight a theme with the chips. Hover for details; click through to the Anthology. Everything here is generated from the same data behind the <a href="/anthology.html">Anthology</a>.</p>

  {# First-visit welcome strip (#1134). Rendered hidden; the inline head
     script above reveals it pre-paint on a first visit, and anthology-
     atlas.js reconciles the hidden attribute + wires the buttons. #}
  <aside class="atlas-welcome" id="atlas-welcome" role="region" aria-labelledby="atlas-welcome-title" hidden>
    <h2 class="atlas-welcome-title" id="atlas-welcome-title">👋 First time on the Atlas?</h2>
    <p class="atlas-welcome-lede">This is an interactive map of the whole <strong>Anthology</strong> — {{ anthologyAtlas.papers | length }} papers across {{ anthologyAtlas.years | length }} editions, drawn to {{ anthologyAtlas.themes | length }} research themes. Here's how to read it:</p>
    <ul class="atlas-welcome-tips">
      <li>🔭 <strong>Two lenses</strong>: switch between Papers and Authors at the top.</li>
      <li>🎚️ <strong>Filter</strong> by edition year, or spotlight a research theme, with the chips.</li>
      <li>🟢 <strong>Solid dots</strong> have an Anthology page; hollow rings don't yet.</li>
      <li>🔗 <strong>Hover</strong> any dot for details, and <strong>click</strong> through to the Anthology.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="atlas-welcome-actions">
      <button class="tour-btn tour-btn-primary" type="button" id="atlas-welcome-tour">Take the tour</button>
      <button class="atlas-welcome-dismiss" type="button" id="atlas-welcome-dismiss" aria-controls="atlas-welcome">Got it</button>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-lens" role="group" aria-label="Choose a lens">
    <span class="lbl">Lens</span>
    <!-- lens chips (Papers / Authors) injected by anthology-atlas.js -->
  </div>

  <div class="atlas-stats" id="atlas-stats" aria-label="Anthology statistics"></div>

  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-authoropts" role="group" aria-label="Author options" hidden>
    <!-- "Collaborators only" chip injected by anthology-atlas.js (Authors lens only) -->
  </div>

  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-paperopts" role="group" aria-label="Paper options">
    <!-- "Abstract on file" chip injected by anthology-atlas.js (Papers lens only, #1152) -->
  </div>

  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-years" role="group" aria-label="Filter by edition year">
    <span class="lbl">Editions</span>
    <!-- year chips injected by anthology-atlas.js -->
  </div>
  <div class="atlas-controls" id="atlas-themes" role="group" aria-label="Spotlight a research theme">
    <span class="lbl">Themes</span>
    <!-- theme hub chips injected by anthology-atlas.js -->
  </div>

  <div class="atlas-stage">
    <canvas id="atlas-canvas" aria-label="Force-directed map of the European Security Studies Anthology: every paper drawn toward the research themes it touches, coloured by edition year, with an Authors lens mapping co-authorship between the same people. The same papers and authors are available as filterable lists on the Anthology page."></canvas>
    <div class="atlas-card" id="atlas-card" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </div>
  {# Visible list alternative (#1155): the canvas is opaque to assistive
     technologies, and a plain list suits plenty of sighted readers too. #}
  <p class="muted" style="margin: var(--space-3) 0 0; font-size: var(--fs-sm);">
    Prefer a list? Every paper and author on this map is browsable in <a href="/anthology.html">the Anthology</a>.
  </p>
  <div class="atlas-legend" id="atlas-legend">
    <span><span class="sw sw-page"></span>has an Anthology page</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-nopage"></span>programme entry only (no page yet)</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-ring sw-prize"></span>Best Paper Prize</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-pub"></span>published version on record</span>
    <span>drag a theme hub to rearrange the map</span>
  </div>
  <div class="atlas-legend" id="atlas-legend-authors" hidden>
    <span><span class="sw sw-collab"></span>author with a co-author</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-solo"></span>solo-only author</span>
    <span><span class="sw sw-coauthor"></span>co-authored a paper together</span>
    <span>dot size scales with paper count</span>
    <span>drag a theme hub to rearrange the map</span>
  </div>
</div>

